instruction:
Find a real number $c$ and a positive number $L$ for which \[ \lim_{r\to\infty} \frac{r^c \int_0^{\pi/2} x^r \sin x \,dx}{\int_0^{\pi/2} x^r \cos x \,dx} = L \] and return the product of $c$ and $L$.

Options:
A. \frac{-1}{2\pi}
B. \frac{-1}{\pi^2}
C. \frac{-4}{\pi}
D. \frac{-3}{\pi}
E. \frac{-2}{\pi}
F. \frac{-1}{\pi}
G. \frac{-3}{2\pi}
